  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_0' aria-label=\" Ajwar versus Waseem and Another R1: Waseem R2: State of Uttar Pradesh pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('0','2025','2025_7_2062_2072','2025INSC968'); ><font size='4'> <strong>AJWAR<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>WASEEM AND ANOTHER R1: WASEEM R2: STATE OF UTTAR PRADESH </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 7 S.C.R. 2062</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 968</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010008302025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : AHSANUDDIN AMANULLAH, SARASA VENKATANARAYANA BHATTI</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Issue arose as regards the correctness of the impugned order passed by the High Court granting bail to respondent no.1-accused. Headnotes&dagger; Bail &ndash; Cancellation of Bail &ndash; Supreme Court cancelled the bail of respondents-accused granted by the High Court to move for bail afresh in event of any new circumstances emerging at a later stage &ndash; Earlier also the High Court had granted bail and in appeal thereagainst this Court had remanded back the matter &ndash; In terms with the order passed by the Supreme Court, the respondent no. 1 applied<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 29-07-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 3232/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('0','2025','2025_7_2062_2072','2025INSC968','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-seco